European Stocks Advance for a Seventh Day Before Jobs Report; Wimpey Gains

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-03-31T07:06:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/european-stocks-advance-for-a-seventh-day-before-jobs-report-wimpey-gains.html
European stocks climbed for a
seventh day before reports on U.S. initial jobless claims and
factory orders. Asian shares rallied, while U.S. futures were
little changed.  Taylor Wimpey Plc  climbed 4.9 percent after agreeing to
sell its North American units for $955 million to cut debt and
buy U.K. land. Hennes & Mauritz AB slumped 4.3 percent after
saying first-quarter profit fell. Bank of Ireland Plc and Irish
Life & Permanent Plc were suspended as the lenders may have to
raise capital after stress tests are published today, said five
people with knowledge of the matter.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index advanced 0.2 percent
to 279.08 at 8:04 a.m. in  London . Standard & Poorâ€™s 500 Index
futures expiring in June climbed 0.1 percent to 1,325.5. The
MSCI Asia Pacific Index jumped 0.7 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
